name: Natasha
descHash: A doctor from the Underworld and a caregiver of children. Alongside her kindness and caring, she also has a hidden dangerous side.

29328.name: Credit
29328.desc: This currency, used by the Interastral Peace Corporation to settle accounts with its customers, is now widely accepted as the hard currency for space travel.
29328.lore: "People run around fighting and trading for numbers in a terminal, but the truly precious cannot be bought."

125435.name: Tracks of Destiny
125435.lore: Your victory is secured by countless failures, and the small steps you have taken led you to the turning point of fate.

270195.name: Guardian's Lament
270195.lore:
Together with this visor, the twisted wish of a Guardian also lies broken.
She had wanted to find a way out for her people to escape the Everwinter, but ended up becoming a puppet of a consciousness beyond her.

"Supreme Guardian, the title passed down to generations of Belobog's rulers, the one who looked after all the people — It never occurred to anyone that the Guardians themselves also long for care and protection."

409960.name: Traveler's Guide
409960.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>20,000</nobr> Character EXP.
409960.lore:
Required reading for world exploration. Press the "Read" button to tune in to an attractive voice in a language you understand, telling you about the legendary encounters of renowned adventurers across different worlds as well as the precious wisdom and knowledge that they have gathered.

"All-new series of the Traveler's Guide, The Chef's Manual to Galactic Cuisine, is now available for purchase."
"For submissions, please connect to synesthesia beacon ERD-23θ to contact an Intelligentsia Guild representative. Method of payment can be arranged to your convenience."

409961.name: Adventure Log
409961.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>5000</nobr> Character EXP.
409961.lore:
A neatly organized collection of educational adventure notes containing countless illustrations and texts entailing adventures from beginning to end, as well as valuable information and survival-related techniques.

"Why not just digitize it and save it on a photolith disk? That'd be much more convenient."
"Advanced technology is far more fragile than you'd think when faced with stellar storms and neuron flow eruptions. Besides, I'm sure the author of this book wanted people to read it in the simplest of ways."

409962.name: Travel Encounters
409962.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>1000</nobr> Character EXP.
409962.lore:
A travel diary with messy handwriting and random content. It's not of much use to you.

"Dan Heng, hurry up and finish reading it so you can throw it away."

549408.name: Ancient Part
549408.desc: Mechanical part left behind from the Old World. Crude material used for enhancement.
549408.lore:
Despite its size, it was cast and polished in a way that people today would struggle to replicate.

"A small screw in the Old World is stronger than our armor."
comeFrom: Robot Settlement: Automatons or other enemies
Great Mine: Automatons or other enemies

633349.name: Ancient Spindle
633349.desc: Mechanical spindle left behind from the Old World. Normal material used for enhancement.
633349.lore:
Once taken apart, the precision components can never be put back together. Even the maintenance veterans in Belobog's Technology Division would think twice before touching it.

"You idiot, the Bluecoats will only give you a few canned goods for this. Take it to Boss Svarog and you won't need to worry about food and clothing for a while."
comeFrom: Robot Settlement: Equilibrium Level 2+ Automatons or other enemies
Great Mine: Equilibrium Level 2+ Automatons or other enemies

635671.name: Seed of Abundance
635671.desc: A seed of blessing sown by the Aeon of Abundance. Used to level up Traces slightly for Abundance characters.
635671.lore:
Those who come in contact with it are slowly healed of their wounds and illnesses.
People who pray for the blessing of life while in despair will always have their prayers answered.

"You shall be granted what you ask for."

717290.name: Ancient Engine
717290.desc: Mechanical engine left behind from the Old World. Advanced material used for enhancement.
717290.lore:
It uses Geomarrow as the energy source. When powered, it spews wandering auroras, not sparkles.

"Only the Technology Division directly under the Supreme Guardian has access to information regarding the Old World. I lost my privileges after I was fired."
comeFrom: Robot Settlement: Equilibrium Level 4+ Automatons or other enemies
Great Mine: Equilibrium Level 4+ Automatons or other enemies

836257.name: Flower of Eternity
836257.desc: A gorgeous flower blooming from the Sprout of Life. Used to level up Traces significantly for Abundance characters.
836257.lore:
The stamen contains the concentrated power of the Path of Abundance, ensuring the flower's ever-lasting vitality. No fire, ice, or any harshness can hinder the growth of this magnificent life form.
Given time, its leaves shall feed upon starlight. Its roots shall burrow into the flesh of every being of this world, all-connected, never-perishing. Its fruits shall fulfill the promise of immortality.

"There be giant ships, eclipsing mountains, drifting over the void. Upon them grows the undying tree. Its consumption grants immortality."

866633.name: Broken Teeth of Iron Wolf
866633.desc: Fragmented saw teeth left behind by automatons. Can be used for the Ascension of Physical characters.
866633.lore:
It is said that the smelting techniques of the Architects allowed them to make chainsaws sturdy enough to split giant boulders. Such techniques have been long lost to history.

"Boss Svarog says its blade is so thin that it can cut into the gap between molecules... What are molecules?"

920198.name: Sprout of Life
920198.desc: A young sprout emerging from the Seed of Abundance. Used to level up Traces moderately for Abundance characters.
920198.lore:
Radiating warmth, life and growth flourish around the place where it sinks its roots. Barren wastelands turn into luscious grass fields, withered plants rejuvenate and blossom, and springs burst through the ground to moisten the land.
As you get closer to it, your muscles and bones twitch and propagate with an unbearable itch.

"Life is unfailing where the soul abounds."

ranks.name: Pharmacology Expertise
ranks.descHash: After being attacked, if the current HP percentage is <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> or lower, heals self for 1 time to restore HP by an amount equal to <nobr>#2[i]%</nobr> of Max HP plus <nobr>#3[i]</nobr>. This effect can only be triggered 1 time per battle.

ranks.name: Clinical Research
ranks.descHash: When Natasha uses her Ultimate, grant continuous healing for <nobr>#2[i]</nobr> turn(s) to allies whose HP is at <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> or lower. And at the beginning of their turn, their HP is restored by an amount equal to <nobr>#3[i]%</nobr> of Natasha's Max HP plus <nobr>#4[i]</nobr>.

ranks.name: The Right Cure
ranks.descHash:
Skill Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Basic ATK Lv. +1, up to a maximum of Lv. 10.

ranks.name: Miracle Cure
ranks.descHash: After being attacked, regenerates <nobr>#1[i]</nobr> extra Energy.

ranks.name: Preventive Treatment
ranks.descHash:
Ultimate Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Talent Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.

ranks.name: Doctor's Grace
ranks.descHash: Natasha's Basic ATK deals Additional Physical DMG equal to <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> of her Max HP.

skills.name: Behind the Kindness
skills.descHash: Deals Physical DMG equal to #1[i]% of Natasha's ATK to a single enemy.

skills.name: Love, Heal, and Choose
skills.descHash: Restores a single ally for #1[f1]% of Natasha's Max HP plus #4[i]. Restores the ally for another #2[f1]% of Natasha's Max HP plus #5[i] at the beginning of each turn for #3[i] turn(s).

skills.name: Gift of Rebirth
skills.descHash: Heals all allies for #1[f1]% of Natasha's Max HP plus #2[i].

skills.name: Innervation
skills.descHash: When healing allies with HP percentage at #1[i]% or lower, increases Natasha's Outgoing Healing by #2[i]%. This effect also works on continuous healing.

skills.name: Attack
skills.descHash: Attack an enemy, and when the battle starts, reduce their Toughness of the corresponding Type.

skills.name: Hypnosis Research
skills.descHash:
Immediately attacks the enemy. After entering battle, deals Physical DMG equal to #4[i]% of Natasha's ATK to a random enemy, with a #1[i]% base chance to Weaken all enemies.
While Weakened, enemies deal #2[i]% less DMG to allies for #3[i] turn(s).

embedBonusSkill.name: Soothe
embedBonusSkill.descHash: The Skill removes <nobr>#1[i]</nobr> debuff(s) from a target ally.

embedBonusSkill.name: Recuperation
embedBonusSkill.descHash: Increases the duration of Skill's continuous healing effect for <nobr>#1[i]</nobr> turn(s).

voiceItems.title: First Meeting
voiceItems.text: Nice to meet you, I'm Natasha — an Underworld doctor. Feeling sick? Take a seat, let me take a look.

voiceItems.title: Greeting
voiceItems.text: I'm in today. But that is not an excuse for misbehavior.

voiceItems.title: About Self
voiceItems.text: I see all kinds of patients. Some require a gentle touch, others need a stern talking to before they take things seriously... Haha, a doctor should always use the right cure for the right person.

voiceItems.title: Chat: Medicine
voiceItems.text: A patient's medicine doesn't just reveal their illness. It also offers a window into their desires and needs.

voiceItems.title: Chat: Wildfire
voiceItems.text: People join Wildfire for themselves, for the newborn next door without a mother, for the elderly with no home to return to.

voiceItems.title: Hobbies
voiceItems.text: I still occasionally practice suturing on my old teddy bear, just like in the old days.

voiceItems.title: Annoyances
voiceItems.text: People in the Underworld have gotten used to making the best of a bad situation. That's why I have to keep reminding myself that we're nowhere near where we need to be.

voiceItems.title: Something to Share
voiceItems.text: Humans long for freedom. If they go for too long without seeing the sky, they get ill... Both in body and mind.

voiceItems.title: Knowledge
voiceItems.text: When the childrens' parents are away in the mines, the clinic becomes a kind of nursery... Haha, to be fair, it's me who invites them. Perhaps I need them more than they need me.

voiceItems.title: About Seele
voiceItems.text: Seele's already become a capable adult — I can't treat her like a child anymore.

voiceItems.title: About Clara
voiceItems.text: I heard she's been looking after the wounded vagrants. What a girl... When I first met Clara, she was replacing parts for her robots like a mechanic, but leaving her own wounds unattended. It was heartbreaking to watch.

voiceItems.title: About Svarog
voiceItems.text: Svarog wants to preserve humanity, but he's not concerned about what humans truly think.

voiceItems.title: About Sampo
voiceItems.text: If I know Sampo, the last thing he wants is to owe you a favor — he'll think of any way possible to pay you back... The longer you leave a favor, the harder it is to calculate its value.

voiceItems.title: About Hook
voiceItems.text: Sometimes I stand at the door of the clinic and watch her running and jumping around... and my tiredness simply goes away.

voiceItems.title: About Oleg
voiceItems.unlockRequirement: Unlocked after completing Trailblaze Mission "The Return."

storyItems.title: Character Details
storyItems.text:
A fastidious doctor who always wears an enigmatic smile.
In the Underworld where medical resources are scarce, Natasha is one of the very few doctors whom the people can turn to.
Even the rambunctious Hook would politely greet her... "Hi, big sis Natasha."
